      <h2>1. What makes a lead generation tool actually worth using</h2>

      <p>Before the picks: the five criteria we apply when evaluating whether a tool is genuinely useful for online business builders versus just broadly functional. A tool can be technically capable and still wrong for this context.</p>

      <div class="criteria-grid">
        <div class="criteria-item">
          <div class="ci-num">01</div>
          <h4>Does one job well</h4>
          <p>Tools that claim to do everything tend to do nothing well. The best tools in our picks are purpose-built: they solve a specific problem in the lead generation chain and solve it reliably.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="criteria-item">
          <div class="ci-num">02</div>
          <h4>Affiliate-friendly terms</h4>
          <p>Many email and landing page platforms restrict promotional affiliate content. A tool that suspends your account for standard affiliate marketing copy is useless for this context, regardless of its other features.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="criteria-item">
          <div class="ci-num">03</div>
          <h4>Accessible to beginners</h4>
          <p>Setup time, learning curve, and onboarding quality matter. A tool that requires a developer or a week of configuration is the wrong tool until you have validated your offer and need the advanced functionality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="criteria-item">
          <div class="ci-num">04</div>
          <h4>Cost relative to stage</h4>
          <p>The right price depends on where you are. A $300/month enterprise platform is wrong at list size zero. A free tool with feature limits that block your next step is also wrong. We flag the threshold at which each tool starts making financial sense.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="criteria-item">
          <div class="ci-num">05</div>
          <h4>Honest lead quality</h4>
          <p>Tools that generate lead counts through scraping, incentivised opt-ins, or low-intent giveaways produce lists that do not convert. We distinguish between tools that build genuine subscriber relationships and tools that inflate numbers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="criteria-item">
          <div class="ci-num">06</div>
          <h4>Deliverability and compliance</h4>
          <p>Email tools specifically need strong deliverability infrastructure. A platform with poor sender reputation means your carefully written follow-up sequence lands in spam — defeating the purpose of capturing the lead in the first place.</p>
        </div>
